HEADWORD: Graptolite
<hw>Grap"to*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL,
Graptolithus, from Gr. <?/ is engraved, written (<grk>gra`fein</grk> to
write) + <?/ stone.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>One of numerous
species of slender and delicate fossils, of the genus
<gen>Graptolites</gen> and allied genera, found in the Silurian rocks.
They belong to an extinct group (<fam>Graptolithina</fam>) supposed to
be hydroids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graptolitic</ent>⟦br⟧
